The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New Delhi, June 4 (PTI): The family of a woman, who died due to overdose of anaesthesia during a gall bladder operation, have been awarded Rs 5 lakh as compensation by Delhi State Consumer Commission.

 Directing Ansari Hospital, a west Delhi-based nursing home, to pay the amount in a month to the husband and minor son of 26-year-old deceased, the commission rejected its plea that 4.3 per cent patients could die after administration of anaesthesia.

 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has directed a Kerala-based hotelier to pay Rs 23.59 lakh as damages to Hilton International for illegally using a trade name similar to that of the hotel chain. K.V. Kumars hotel is called Hilten.

 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): An 80-year-old man married his domestic help despite opposition from his two sons. Rakam Singh married Saloni, 40, in a court at Gauri Pukhta town nearby. But the sons, both sub-inspectors, threw their step-mother out of the house.

 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has issued a notice to former chief minister Amarinder Singhs son Raninder on a petition filed by the Punjab government. The petition challenged the grant of anticipatory bail to him in the Ludhiana City Centre scam case. 

 New Delhi (PTI): A moderate intensity earthquake measuring 5.2 on Richter scale struck Nicobar islands on Monday. The tremor struck at 6.52 in the morning, the meteorological office said. There was no report of any casualty or loss of property.

 Nagpur (PTI): The forest conservator of North Chandrapur circle was caught by the anti-corruption bureau accepting Rs 2.20 lakh from a contractor for issuing a transport permit. The team also seized Rs 13.45 lakh in cash from Ravindra Mohan Dayals car at his residence, police said.




